section.text:
Notwithstanding 
          section 1337 of the Federal Housing Enterprises Financial Safety and Soundness Act of 1992 (
          12 U.S.C. 4567
        ) or any other provision of law, during the term of any conservatorship or receivership of the Federal National Mortgage Association or the Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corporation pursuant to 
          section 1367 of such Act (
          12 U.S.C. 4617
        ), such enterprise shall not make any contribution or transfer to, or allocate or set aside any amounts for, the Housing Trust Fund established under 
          section 1338 of such Act (
          12 U.S.C. 4568
        ) or the Capital Magnet Fund established under 
          section 1339 of such Act (
          12 U.S.C. 4569
        ).
